  walkthrough: `The Chemotherapy fortress rises from the north-west bastion of Pharma City, its thick stone walls rising above a deep moat. Each gate is a category: the Cell-Wall Gate admits the β-lactams — penicillin, amoxicillin, ceftriaxone — whose swords shatter bacterial transpeptidases; beside it the Glycopeptide Redoubt houses vancomycin's red-robed sentinels, famed for the Red Man flush when they rush the battlements. The Protein-Synthesis Sentry Tower rises above the moat, home to the ribosome-silencers — macrolides on the 50S walkway, aminoglycosides lobbing irreversible ototoxic grenades from the 30S platform, tetracyclines barring the 30S gate, clindamycin crouching on the MLSB ledge, linezolid at the 23S radio mast. The DNA Library occupies the fortress keep: fluoroquinolones block the topoisomerase locks; metronidazole's nitroimidazole agents work only in anaerobic darkness. The Mycobacterial Side Fort stands beyond the moat — RIPE soldiers drilled in four disciplines (isoniazid the peripheral-nerve risk, rifampicin the orange flag-carrier, pyrazinamide the gout-raiser, ethambutol the colour-blind watchman). Beyond the side fort lie specialist armories: the Antifungal Armory (amphotericin's black polyene cannon, fluconazole's CYP-blocking azole trebuchet, voriconazole's visual-distortion cannon, caspofungin's glucan-wall demolisher), the Antiviral Pavilion (acyclovir's crystal-dripping aqueduct, oseltamivir's neuraminidase-snipping scissors, and the HIV quarter with its NRTIs, NNRTIs, integrase inhibitors, and pharmacokinetic-booster ritonavir), and the Antimalarial Arsenal (chloroquine's crystalline stockpile, artemether-lumefantrine's fast-strike combination, primaquine's G6PD-hazardous reserve supply).

The Anticancer War Room occupies the highest tower inside the fortress, its walls mapped with cytotoxic battle orders: methotrexate folds the folate supply lines, cyclophosphamide's alkylating bombs demand the mesna fire-brigade for haemorrhagic cystitis, cisplatin's platinum-tipped shells call for saline hydration against nephrotoxicity and ototoxicity, doxorubicin's anthracycline cannonade is counted by the cardiomyopathy dose-meter, vincristine tangles the tubulin cables leaving peripheral nerves silenced, paclitaxel stabilises the tubulin scaffolding until it collapses under hypersensitivity reactions, 5-fluorouracil scorches the mucosa and the hands-feet in hand-foot syndrome. On the parapets of the tower stand the targeted generals: imatinib blockades the BCR-ABL tyrosine kinase drawbridge of CML, rituximab's anti-CD20 monoclonal banner warns of HBV reactivation, bevacizumab's anti-VEGF banner streams in a hypertensive wind. Below the war room, the Immunomodulator Barracks house cyclosporine, tacrolimus, mycophenolate, azathioprine, and infliximab — each with its own watch-post for nephrotoxicity, opportunistic infection, TB reactivation, and teratogenicity. Over the central turret, the fortress flag waves in the wind — a signal to all enemies of the body that its defences are mobilised.`,
